<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 1: MOUNTING ENGINE ON STAND - REMOVING
        OIL COOLER ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REMOVING OIL COOLER ASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Remove oil cooler and water coolant supply tube as an assembly.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
            <title>Remove Oil Cooler</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove one (1) bolt and retainer plate securing water coolant supply tube from crankcase
                    (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600107">1.7</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove mounting hardware securing oil cooler assembly to crankcase (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600107">1.7</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1600107" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5037" filename="../figeg5/eg5037.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1.7 Remove Oil Cooler Mounting Hardware</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">1. Retainer Plate and Mounting Bolt</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">2. Oil Cooler</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">3. Oil Cooler Mounting Hardware</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove oil cooler and water coolant supply tube as an assembly from crankcase and
                    discard O-Rings (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600108">1.8</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1600108" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5039" filename="../figeg5/eg5039.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1.8 Remove Oil Cooler</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove oil pressure regulating valve assembly from the crankcase. Depress valve plunger
                    and insert a copper wire, release plunger to trap wire in the valve. Pull out (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e160_40.xml" xrefid="ef1600109">1.9</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>THE OIL PRESSURE REGULATING VALVE SHOULD BE TAGGED UPON REMOVAL TO ENSURE IDENTIFICATION.
                            DO NOT MIX OIL PRESSURE REGULATOR VALVE WITH high OIL PRESSURE RELIEF VALVE (FOUND IN FRONT
                            COVER).
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
